Rating: 4
I made this olive loaf for a church coffee hour. There was none left over. Congregants asked for the recipe. I always soak olives in water before using them to remove unwanted saltiness. I also use exceptional flour from the Great Valley Mills in Pennsylvania, suppliers of flour to Gen. Washington at Valley Forge in 1777-1778. I will definitely make this recipe again and again.

Rating: 2
I thought that this recipe was good, however, I didn't put all the basil in it, only about half. I also put half ripe olives and half green. My guests that it was an interesting alternative bread choice. It was easy to make and very eye appealing.

