Rating: 3
I had read the previous comments for this, and made some modifications to the recipe: instead of 1 cup olives, I used slightly less than 1/2 cup; a little less than 1/4 cup oil; used 8 egg whites and 3 egg yolks; no salt at all; and a little extra baking powder. And it came out really good.

Rating: 2
This bread was, indeed, veeery dense. The taste was actually quite good, but the texture was just a little odd. I probably won't make it again--I have better recipes--but my husband thought it was wonderful!

Rating: 1
I fixed this bread for a Greek theme potluck. I didn't much care for this bread. I love all ingredients in it but this bread came out too salty, too dense... Like you said in your description of this recipe... smells good , and is lovely to look at...that seems to be all. I probably would cut the amount of Greek olives to 1/2 cup instead of one.